"title": "5267: control",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5267",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The exercise of authority and restraint over individuals and events. Scripture stresses that God is in sovereign control over his creation. A limited degree of control over creation is delegated to humanity.</p>\n<h2>God controls the whole world</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1\">GEN 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:3\">GEN 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:6\">NEH 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:25\">PSA 102:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:3\">HEB 11:3</a></p>\n<h2>God controls the affairs of heaven and earth</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:39\">DEU 4:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:35\">DAN 4:35</a></p>\n<h3>He gives wealth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:18\">DEU 8:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:12\">1CH 29:12</a></p>\n<h3>He appoints and deposes earthly rulers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:6-Ps75:7\">PSA 75:6–75:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:21\">DAN 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:17\">DAN 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:32\">DAN 4:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:18\">DAN 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:21\">DAN 5:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:26\">DAN 5:26</a></p>\n<h3>He controls human hearts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:1\">PRO 21:1</a></p>\n<h3>He controls times and seasons</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:22\">GEN 8:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:15\">PSA 31:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:21\">DAN 2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:9\">AMO 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:7\">ACT 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>He controls the weather</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:7\">AMO 4:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:45\">MAT 5:45</a></p>\n<h3>He saves those whom he wills</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:11-Rom9:16\">ROM 9:11–9:16</a></p>\n<h3>He fixes human destiny</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34\">MAT 25:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41\">MAT 25:41</a></p>\n<h2>Human control over creation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:28\">GEN 1:26–1:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:15\">GEN 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:19-Gen2:20\">GEN 2:19–2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:16-Gen3:19\">GEN 3:16–3:19</a> <em>After the fall it became difficult for human beings to control creation.</em></p>\n<h2>Human control over earthly territories</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:1\">JOS 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1\">2SA 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:3\">2SA 8:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr17:5\">2CH 17:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:43\">DAN 11:43</a></p>\n<h2>Both the godly and ungodly should control themselves</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:32\">PRO 16:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:11\">PRO 29:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:9\">1CO 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:37\">1CO 7:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:5\">2CO 10:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:4\">1TH 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>Prophecy should be under the control of the prophets</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:32\">1CO 14:32</a></p>\n<h2>The evil one has limited control</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:19\">1JN 5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:6-Job1:7\">JOB 1:6–1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:12\">EPH 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13\">COL 1:13</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ will have final control over all things</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:21\">PHP 3:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24-1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:24–15:28</a> <em>Jesus Christ himself will be finally made subject to God.</em></p>",
